        K - Covered patterns in the second stage are completely eliminated when they have been covered more than K times.

    • Method Detail

      • incCount

        public void incCount()
        Increments in 1 the number of times that it has been covered. If this number exceed the value K after been incremented, it is completely eliminated, reducing the weight to 0. Otherwise the weight is updated inversely proportional to the times covered.

      • getCount

        public int getCount()
        Returns the number of times counted.
        Returns:
        Number of times counted.

      • isActive

        public boolean isActive()
        Checks if the pattern is active. This means checking if the number of times counted are smaller than the fixed K.
        Returns:
        True if the number of times counted are smaller than the fixed K. False otherwise.

      • getWeight

        public double getWeight()
        Returns the weight given to the pattern.
        Returns:
        the weight given to the pattern
